    "original_title": "Manhattan: 3rd Avenue - 113th Street",
    "text": "2065 to 2069 Third Ave., (left, elevated line thereon), at, adjoining and north of the N.E. corner of East 113th Street (right), showing prominently 3 tenements forming a 76 X 104 foot plot that will be cleared according to the New York Times of September 22, 1937. This property, a part of the old Bogart farm was purchased by Captain Johannes Benson about 1696 and held in his family until today, being transferred by the estate of Annie W. Gould, a direct descendant. See the aforementioned newspaper for a fuller account.\n\nNovember 14, 1937.\n\nP. L. Sperr.\n",
